        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 3:22PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Waugh Mountain, or 47 miles southwest of Colorado Springs, moving
south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, penny size hail and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Waugh Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
